critical_positive: I think it worked well by talking in detail about our experiences. I feel like she asked a lot of questions and I answered them by providing lots of details and I think I might have appeared to be funny because she was trying not to laugh at my responses.
critical_negative: I think there were a few distractions on my end as I heard neighbors in the background and a family member storming into the room I was in looking for something. There was a slight lag in some parts of the video but it stayed for very little time and was not much of a distraction.

begin_memory_text: We talked about their pharmacy school. I mentioned that my partner is in nursing school. I think that we also talked about their weekend. They went to a pumpkin patch. Their birthday was on Friday.
middle_memory_text: Talked a bit more about pharmacy school. I asked them about sims, etc. Asked if pharmacy school is 2 years or 4 years. Talked a little about our histories with Prolific. Talked a bit about their job.
end_memory_text: Talked about their major in undergrad. I talked a little about the research studies that I did in undergrad. We talked about their experience as a TA for Organic Chemistry lab. Talked about one time when two students spilled stuff in the fume hood, leading to a reaction. The students got yelled at by the teacher.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week as going to same as my previous week. I think that I'll be a little busy with cooking. I also think that I'll stress myself out a little by worrying about "things to do." I hope that it will go OK, overall, though. And I hope that I won't let myself stress too much.
critical_positive: I think that I asked a lot of questions, which helped. I tried to keep the conversation going without too many awkward pauses. When there was an awkward pause, the other person did try to step in with a question. It felt like we both were invested in holding a conversation for the full time and not letting it too awkward.
critical_negative: I feel like I had to ask a lot of questions to get them to talk about stuff. They didn't ask many questions of me, but I was OK with that. It felt like they were reticent to talk for a long length about much of anything, until the end when we were talking about Organic Chemistry. On the other hand, though, I also didn't give many answers when I was asked a question.
